&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fushimi_Castle&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fushimi Castle&lt;/a&gt;, a replica built in 1964, looking out over the mountains (and transmission lines) of southern Kyoto, in this photo taken from Kyoto Tower.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  京都タワーから撮影した、京都南部の山並みを見下ろす&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BC%8F%E8%A6%8B%E5%9F%8E&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;伏見城&lt;/a&gt;。1964年に建てられたレプリカです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Castles" /><summary type="html">Fushimi Castle, a replica built in 1964, looking out over the mountains (and transmission lines) of southern Kyoto, in this photo taken from Kyoto Tower.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02485.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02485.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Higanbana・彼岸花</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220916/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Higanbana・彼岸花" /><published>2022-09-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/higanbana</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220916/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Red spider lilies (Higanbana) in a sea of green, at Daikaku-ji Temple.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  緑色の海にヒガンバナ、大覚寺にて。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Flowers" /><category term="Daikaku-ji" /><summary type="html">Red spider lilies (Higanbana) in a sea of green, at Daikaku-ji Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02447.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02447.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama・嵐山</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220915/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama・嵐山" /><published>2022-09-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220915/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
A sunny afternoon on the river.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
川沿い晴れたの午後。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Boats" /><summary type="html">A sunny afternoon on the river.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_5991.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_5991.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Golden Rails・金色の線路</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220913/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Golden Rails・金色の線路" /><published>2022-09-13T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-13T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/golden-tracks</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220913/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Setting sun lights up the tracks at Kyoto Station.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都駅の線路を照らす夕日。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html">Setting sun lights up the tracks at Kyoto Station.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02409.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02409.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">A Cool Breeze・鴨川の涼しい風</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220912/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="A Cool Breeze・鴨川の涼しい風" /><published>2022-09-12T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-12T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kamogawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220912/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
After sunset, the cool breeze from the Kamogawa River provides a welcome respite from the hot day.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
日没後、鴨川からの涼しい風が暑い一日を癒してくれる感じです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Kamo River" /><summary type="html">After sunset, the cool breeze from the Kamogawa River provides a welcome respite from the hot day.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02397.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02397.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Fog in the Mountains・山の霧</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220911/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fog in the Mountains・山の霧" /><published>2022-09-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/mountain-fog</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220911/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Looking northwest across the Katsura River at Mount Atago. Early morning fog often forms in the the canyons.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
桂川を挟んで北西にある愛宕山を望む。渓谷には早朝に霧が発生することが多い。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Dawn" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Fog" /><summary type="html">Looking northwest across the Katsura River at Mount Atago. Early morning fog often forms in the the canyons.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02381.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02381.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Osaka Station・大阪駅</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220910/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Osaka Station・大阪駅" /><published>2022-09-10T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-10T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/osaka-station</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220910/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
A quiet corridor in an otherwise bustling train station.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
賑やかな駅の中の静かな廊下。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html">A quiet corridor in an otherwise bustling train station.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02317.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02317.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Water Galaxy・水の銀河</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220907/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Water Galaxy・水の銀河" /><published>2022-09-07T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-07T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/water-galaxy</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220907/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
A constellation of water droplets, caught in a spider web.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
蜘蛛の巣に絡まった水滴の星座。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Water" /><summary type="html">A constellation of water droplets, caught in a spider web.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02214.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02214.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama Sunrise</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220906/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama Sunrise" /><published>2022-09-06T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-06T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama-sunrise</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220906/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Sun rises over Kyoto‘s eastern mountains, as a motorcycle drives by on the Togetsu Bridge.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都の東山から昇る朝日と、渡月橋を走るバイク。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Sunrise" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><summary type="html">Sun rises over Kyoto‘s eastern mountains, as a motorcycle drives by on the Togetsu Bridge.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02172-HDR-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02172-HDR-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Blue Machiya・青い町屋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220905/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Blue Machiya・青い町屋" /><published>2022-09-05T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-05T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/blue-machiya</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220905/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Blue Bottle Coffee in a traditional machiya building, at Rokkaku and Higashinotoin Streets in central Kyoto. The coffee shop took over a 100 year old bicycle shop (the bike shop still occupies the left section of the building); while a new multi-story grocery store is next door. This is Kyoto in a nutshell: new and old, co-existing, thriving. (Note the big stone at the corner, commonly used to protect from vehicle traffic.)
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都の六角通と東洞院通にあるブルーボトルコーヒー。このコーヒーショップは、100年以上の歴史を持つ自転車店を引き継ぎ（自転車店はまだ建物の左側部分を占めています）、その隣りを新しい多層階の八百屋が取り囲んでいます。新しいものと古いものが共存し、繁栄している、それが京都なのです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Night" /><category term="Machiya" /><summary type="html">Blue Bottle Coffee in a traditional machiya building, at Rokkaku and Higashinotoin Streets in central Kyoto. The coffee shop took over a 100 year old bicycle shop (the bike shop still occupies the left section of the building); while a new multi-story grocery store is next door. This is Kyoto in a nutshell: new and old, co-existing, thriving. (Note the big stone at the corner, commonly used to protect from vehicle traffic.)</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02099-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02099-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>